{"sessionKey":"42nd3rdju_01","paragraphs":[{"html":"<b><i>TIME</i></b><i> <b>� 5:30 p.m.</b></i>","index":"00000","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>LOCATION � Winnipeg, Manitoba</i></b>","index":"00001","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>CHAIRPERSON � Mr. Andrew Micklefield (Rossmere)</i></b>","index":"00002","speaker":"Andrew Micklefield"},{"html":"<b><i>VICE-CHAIRPERSON �</i></b><i> <b>Ms. Audrey Gordon\n(Southdale)</b></i>","index":"00003","speaker":"Audrey Gordon"},{"html":"<b><i>ATTENDANCE � 6��� QUORUM � 4</i></b>","index":"00004","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Members of the Committee\npresent:</i>","index":"00005","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Hon. Mr. Cullen, Hon. Mrs.\nStefanson</i>","index":"00006","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Mses. Fontaine, Gordon, Mr.\nMicklefield, Mrs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Smith</i>","index":"00007","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>MATTERS UNDER CONSIDERATION:</i></b>","index":"00008","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Bill 9�The Opioid Damages and\nHealth Care Costs Recovery Act</i>","index":"00009","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*\n* *</b>","index":"00010","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Clerk Assistant (Ms. Katerina\nTefft): </b>Good afternoon. Will the Standing Committee on Justice please come\nto order.","index":"00011","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Before the committee can proceed with the business\nbefore it, it must elect a new Chairperson.","index":"00012","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Are there any nominations for this position? ","index":"00013","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms. Audrey Gordon (Southdale):</b> I nominate the member\nfor Rossmere (Mr. Micklefield).�� ","index":"00014","speaker":"Audrey Gordon"},{"html":"<b>Clerk Assistant:</b> Mr. Micklefield has been nominated.�\n","index":"00015","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Are there any other nominations?","index":"00016","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Hearing no other nominations, Mr. Micklefield, will\nyou please take the Chair.","index":"00017","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Our next item of business is the\nelection of a new Vice-Chairperson.� ","index":"00018","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Are there any nominations?","index":"00019","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Cliff Cullen (Minister of Justice and Attorney\nGeneral): </b>I nominate Ms. Gordon. ","index":"00020","speaker":"Cliff Cullen"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Ms. Gordon has been nominated.� ","index":"00021","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Are there any other nominations?","index":"00022","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Hearing no other nominations, Ms. Gordon is elected\nVice-Chairperson.","index":"00023","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This meeting has been called to consider Bill 9, The\nOpioid Damages and Health Care Costs Recovery Act. ","index":"00024","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>����� </b>We have no registered presenters to this bill.<b>\n</b>","index":"00025","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> We will now proceed with\nclause-by-clause of Bill 9. ","index":"00026","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Does the minister responsible for Bill 9 have any�have\nan opening statement? ","index":"00027","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon. Cliff Cullen (Minister of Justice and Attorney\nGeneral):</b> Mr. Chair, just briefly. I'm pleased to have introduced this\nlegislation, which will allow Manitoba to join a class action lawsuit that was\nlaunched by British Columbia in 2018. This lawsuit aims to hold to account\nopioid manufacturers whose products have had and continue to have damaging\neffects on the health and well-being of Manitobans.","index":"00028","speaker":"Cliff Cullen"},{"html":"����� Once passed, Manitoba would\njoin British&nbsp;Columbia, Alberta, Saskatchewan, Ontario, Newfoundland and\nLabrador, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick in pursuing action against the opioid\nindustry.","index":"00029","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This builds on our\ngovernment's investments in expanding the continuum of care for mental health\nand addictions related to�related challenges in our province and aligns with recommendations\nof a number of reports including VIRGO, the Illicit Drug Task Force and the\nCommunity Wellness and Public Safety Alliance reports. ","index":"00030","speaker":""},{"html":"����� I look forward to the support\nof the committee and the House in having this bill passed so that we can take\non pharmaceutical companies that have created such a significant and ongoing\nharm to Manitobans.","index":"00031","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Thank you, Mr. Chair. ","index":"00032","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> We thank the minister. ","index":"00033","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Does the critic from the official opposition have an\nopening statement? ","index":"00034","speaker":""},{"html":"����� During the consideration of a bill, the enacting\nclause and title are postponed until all other clauses have been considered in\ntheir proper order.","index":"00035","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Also, if there is agreement from the committee, the\nChair will call clauses in blocks that conform to pages, with the understanding\nthat we will stop at any particular clause or clauses where members may have\ncomments, questions or amendments to propose. Is that agreed? <i>[Agreed]</i>","index":"00036","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>����� </i>I now invite all virtual committee members to\nunmute themselves so that their responses to the question can be heard. ","index":"00037","speaker":""},{"html":"As a reminder to all, the members\nof this committee are myself; Honourable Mr. Cullen; Ms.&nbsp;Fontaine; Ms.\nGordon; Mrs. Smith, Point Douglas; and Honourable Mrs. Stefanson.","index":"00038","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Clause 1�pass; clause 2�pass; clause 3�pass; clause\n4�pass; clause 5�pass; clauses 6 and 7�pass; clause 8�pass; clauses 9 through\n11�pass; clauses 12 and 13�pass; clauses 14 and 15�pass; schedule�pass;\nenacting clause�pass; title�pass. Bill be reported. ","index":"00039","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>����� </b>The hour being 5:35, what is the will of the\ncommittee? ","index":"00040","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some Honourable Members:</b> Rise. ","index":"00041","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Committee rise. ","index":"00042","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>COMMITTEE ROSE AT:</i></b><i>\n5:35 p.m.</i> ","index":"00043","speaker":""}]}